sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1627009
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Enhanced Yellow Fluorescent Protein, with Medium Promoter and RBS
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
This is a plasmid using the pSB1C3 backbone, which is composed of the CamR resistance gene and the pMB1 origin of replication. A vector was inserted into the plasmid backbone,BBa_K608006 (J23110 + B0032), which is composed of the Bio-Brick promoter BBa_J23110 and ribosome binding site BBa_B0032. A fluorescent protein gene was then inserted into the resulting plasmid. BBa_E0030, the Enhanced Yellow Fluorescent Protein gene was the fluorescent gene inserted in the plasmid.
This plasmid allows the creation of the enhanced yellow fluorescent protein inside bacteria.
This plasmid (BBa_K1627009) was used in the study of stability of genetic devices across generations by the 2015 University of Texas at Austin iGEM team. The plasmid has been observed be remain genetically stable across one-hundred generations.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Devin Wehle
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This plasmid was constructed from previously constructed Biobrick parts. The pSB1C3 backbone, BBa_K608006 vector, and the BBa_E0030 Enhanced Yellow Fluorescent Protein.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The plasmid was constructed and cloned from parts from the Biobrick registry.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0032
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Weak1 RBS based on Ron Weiss thesis. Strength is considered relative to <bb_part>BBa_B0030</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0031</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0033</bb_part>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix ("RBS-2" in figure 4-14 of thesis).

Contact info for this part: Brian Chow
